<p style="text-align: justify">
<b>Short Description:</b> This project focuses on developing approaches for generating understandable explanations for complex decision-making processes, particularly in high-stakes domains like law and medicine. We make use of graphs to represent the data and the interconnections within data. This is expected to help in unraveling complex connections and patterns for a deeper understanding of multifaceted relationships; 
Interpretable Applications. Such approaches are particularly beneficial where decisions involve weighing multiple factors, allowing for better analysis and more robust decision-making. The project aims to not only make accurate predictions but also to generate human-understandable explanations for these predictions.
